<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7356> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7356" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q(uaestor ad) A(erarium)? See MRR 2.287. Since no Pompeian quaestor was elected to office after 50, Sumner rejects Grant's view that this man was a Pompeian quaestor in Africa in 47 or 46, and suggests that if Grant is correct about the office Pomp(onius) must be regarded as a quaestor of 49 who continued for two years as pro quaestore (Phoenix 25, 1971, 263)\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5737> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5737" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q(uaestor ad) A(erarium?), a Pompeian in Africa in 47 or 46 (Grant, From Imperium to Auctoritas 20f.)." .
